body: I didn't have time to dig into the code, therefore no. But since C++ tests are passing, I guess that they have changed something in the C++ implementation without reflecting the changes in the tensorflow tests (maybe some operation that fist was accepting a `float32` now needs a `float64`). I'm pretty sure that other packages that depend on the go package could still work. Tomorrow I'm going to try if [tfgo](https://github.com/galeone/tfgo) can still be built and run. I keep you up-to-date
